SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 846
By Bailey
A RESOLUTION to honor Jerry Maynord on being inducted into
the Tennessee Football Coaches Association
Hall of Fame.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in paying tribute
to those gifted coaches who have attained the very pinnacle of sporting achievement; and
WHEREAS, Jerry Maynord is one such legendary high school football coach, who was
recently inducted into the Tennessee Football Coaches Association Hall of Fame as a member
of the Class of 2026; and
WHEREAS, an iconic figure within his community, Jerry Maynord won nearly two-thirds
of the games he coached, compiling a 234-126 overall record during a remarkable career that
spanned forty-two years; and
WHEREAS, in 2021, he retired as the head coach at Cookeville High School, where he
had led the football program for nine years; and
WHEREAS, Coach Maynord's best season at Cookeville was in 2017, when he led the
Cavaliers to a 10-3 record and playoff wins over Rossview and Riverdale; and
WHEREAS, Jerry Maynord's outstanding coaching career also included tenures at three
other Tennessee high schools, White County, Upperman, and Smith County; and
WHEREAS, in 2024, Coach Maynord returned to Upperman to serve as the school's
athletic director; and
WHEREAS, Jerry Maynord demonstrated peerless leadership and tactical skill
throughout his long and distinguished coaching career, and it is fitting that we should recognize
him on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
SJR0846
013820
- 1 -

REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Jerry Maynord on being
inducted into the Tennessee Football Coaches Association Hall of Fame as a member of its
Class of 2026 and extend to him our best wishes for much continued success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
